2. cs.RO (Robotics): The techniques and tools presented in the paper can be applied to the design of control software for robots, which falls under the Robotics sub-category. 
3. cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The focus of the paper is on the design of embedded control software, which is a key topic in the Embedded Systems sub-category. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the use of static analysis and stochastic local search for synthesizing control software, which can be seen as a programming language-related topic. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper presents a methodology and tool for synthesizing control software, which can be considered as a software engineering topic.
